title: Quality Assurance Engineer
description:
Job Description:

At AT&T we’re redefining the future of communication by connecting people to greater possibility – with expertise, simplicity, and inspiration. At the heart of our purpose lies a diverse workforce of 200,000 people and a culture that aspires to serve customers first, act boldly, move faster, and win as one.

Our Product Development group, part of AT&T’s Technology Services (ATS) organization, is responsible for building software-based products, services, and platforms that our customers love and need. Harnessing technology and rebuilding software expertise, the team is inspiring simplicity with projects that deliver revenue and cost savings opportunities.

Job Overview:

We are looking for a skilled and driven Quality Assurance Engineer to join our team. In this role, you will be instrumental in maintaining the exceptional quality of our back-end and front-end web applications.

Your responsibilities will include designing and executing automated tests, identifying and resolving issues, defining corrective measures, reviewing system requirements, and monitoring quality assurance metrics to ensure optimal performance.

Core Responsibilities:

  • Create detailed, comprehensive, and well-structured test plans and test cases
  • Review requirements, specifications, and technical design documents to provide timely and meaningful feedback
  • Estimate, prioritize, plan and coordinate testing activities
  • Design, develop and execute automation scripts
  • Identify, record, document thoroughly and track bugs
  • Perform thorough regression testing when bugs are resolved
  • Work with the US-based Quality Lead to develop and apply testing processes for new and existing products to meet client needs
  • Coordinate with stakeholders and identify system requirements
  • Monitor debugging process results
  • Investigate the causes of non-conforming software and train users to implement solutions
  • Track quality assurance metrics, like defect densities and open defect counts
  • Stay up to date with new testing tools and test strategies


Skills

  • Candidate must have experience as a member of the SCRUM team in the same/similar position.
  • Candidate must have already some experiences with testing tools
  • Candidate should have already some experiences with Test Automation
    • Experience on the level of the test automation architect or programmer is Advantage
  • Technology stack is variable, more important is to be willing and open to learn new technologies. (Windows, Linux, Unix, AZURE, C/C++, C#/.NET, JAVA, Python, TypeScript, Bash, PowerShell, GIT, Some Relational and non-REL DBs such a Mongo, Oracle, MySQL, MS SQL, )
  • Experience with any Testing Frameworks /Libraries (Playwright, Cypress.IO, Pytest, Selenium, Cucumber) advantage
    • Experiences with any object-oriented programing language is an Advantage
  • Candidate must be able to work with standard collaboration tools (JIRA, Confluence, GIT)
  • Experiences with IDE are Advantage (we are using MS Studio CODE)

Location and Work Environment:

Position is based in Bratislava, Slovakia; Kosice, Slovakia; and Brno, Czechia. They are hybrid-flex positions requiring presence in the office 1-3 times per week, with occasional travel between these locations.

Working hours:

EMEA, approx. 9am-5,30pm (with some flexibility)

Compensation:

Salary Range for Slovakia from 3 200 to 4 200 EUR gross monthly.

Salary Range for Czech Republic from 94 600 to 141 000 CZK gross monthly.

The actual offered salary may be considerably higher based on your skills, knowledge, and experience.

Benefits:

A career with us, a global leader in communications and technology, comes with big rewards. We offer a competitive salary plus an annual company performance bonus. Once you are a part of the team, you will gain some amazing perks and benefits including wellness & leisure time contribution, sickness compensation plan, premium medical services, family friendly benefits as well as meal contribution and extra days off (…and much more).

Ready to find out more? Apply today!

Weekly Hours:

40

Time Type:

Regular

Location:

SVK:BL:Bratislava / Einsteinova 24 - Adm:24 Einsteinova

It is the policy of AT&T to provide equal employment opportunity (EEO) to all persons regardless of age, color, national origin, citizenship status, physical or mental disability, race, religion, creed, gender, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity and/or expression, genetic information, marital status, status with regard to public assistance, veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by federal, state or local law. In addition, AT&T will provide reasonable accommodations for qualified individuals with disabilities. AT&T is a fair chance employer and does not initiate a background check until an offer is made.

title: Junior Test Engineer (automation)
description:
Summary

We are looking for an Junior Test Engineer to ensure the quality of security applications for cloud-based solutions. The role involves working closely with software engineers within an agile team to validate their work and contribute to both manual and automated testing, ensuring reliable, secure, and high-quality software delivery.

Position is directly located in Bratislava without the option to work remotely. We require be onsite 2 days per week in average.

Job Description

Responsibilities:

  • Plan, design, execute, and maintain test cases for cloud-based security applications.
  • Collaborate closely with software engineers, product owners, and other agile team members throughout the development lifecycle.
  • Identify, document, and track defects, and verify fixes.
  • Contribute to the design, implementation, and maintenance of automated tests (e.g. unit, integration, and end-to-end tests).
  • Ensure overall product quality with a focus on functionality, performance, reliability, and security.
  • Continuously improve testing processes, tools, and practices within the team.

Minimum Qualifications:

  • Experience in software testing within an agile development environment.
  • Understanding of software development lifecycle and agile methodologies (Scrum/Kanban).
  • Hands-on experience with test design techniques and test execution.
  • Basic knowledge of automated testing concepts and tools (e.g. Selenium, Playwright, or similar).
  • General understanding of cloud-based applications and architectures (e.g. how applications are typically deployed and tested in AWS, Azure, or Google Cloud environments).
  • Analytical thinking, attention to detail, and a collaborative mindset.
  • English language – intermediate proficiency.

Nice to Have:

  • Experience with test automation in C#, PowerShell, or similar scripting or programming languages.
  • Familiarity with API testing (REST, gRPC).
  • Experience with CI/CD pipelines and integrating automated tests into build processes.
  • Basic knowledge of performance and security testing concepts.
  • Experience working with microservice-based systems.

Basic wage component (brutto): from 2300 EUR/m. (brutto)

* The final basic wage component can be increased accordingly to individual skills and experience of the selected candidate.

* Performance bonus 2 times per year up to 10% of the basic salary paid for the evaluation period(usually 6 months).





At ESET, diversity, equity, and inclusion (DEI) are integral to our corporate culture. We believe in creating a respectful environment, where everyone feels valued and respected, welcoming applications from individuals of all backgrounds, including race, gender, age, religion, disability, and sexual orientation.

title: QA Engineer / Sr. QA Engineer - Machine Learning Platform for E-Commerce
description:
AppIQ Tech is seeking a meticulous and strategic QA Engineer / Sr. QA Engineer to ensure the quality and reliability of our Machine-Learning-driven e-commerce funnel optimisation and digital advertising platform.
You will be responsible for defining the testing strategy for high-performance applications that leverage our proprietary Predictive AI solutions.
As a key member of our fast-paced startup, you will balance the need for rapid feature deployment with the necessity of thorough testing. You will be responsible for identifying and prioritising the highest-risk bugs to ensure our scalable services, which manage millions of daily events, remain robust and accurate.
QA Architecture & Strategy: Develop and maintain a comprehensive QA architecture that supports full-stack applications and complex microservices.
Risk Management: Prioritise bug fixes based on risk of failure and potential impact, while striking a productive balance between speed-to-market and exhaustive testing.
Test Management: Utilise test case management (TCM) systems such as TestRail, Zephyr, Xray, PractiTest, qTest, or similar to organise test cases, track execution, and provide transparent reporting on quality metrics.
Automated Testing: Design, implement, and scale automated test suites using tools such as Playwright, Cypress, and Appium.
Testing & Validation: Perform rigorous unit tests and integration tests on applications built with TypeScript, React, Node.js, Python, and PySpark.
Infrastructure Testing: Verify the reliability of deployments across AWS (EC2, S3, Firehose) and Cloudflare edge environments.
Data Integrity: Collaborate with Data Engineers to validate the accuracy of complex event data and real-time reporting dashboards.
Cross-Functional Collaboration: Act as a great team player with excellent communication skills, working closely with developers and data scientists to ensure a seamless end-user experience.
Requirements
4+ years of professional experience in software quality assurance or engineering, with a strong focus on scalable web applications (7+years for Sr. QA Engineer).
Strong grasp of QA architecture and modern testing methodologies.
Deep expertise in the tech stack used by our engineers, specifically TypeScript, React, Node.js, Python, and PySpark.
Cloud & Database Proficiency: Familiarity with AWS services and both SQL and NoSQL (e.g., MongoDB) databases to effectively test data persistence and performance.
Global Collaboration: Ability to work effectively with globally distributed teams.
Native or Business-level proficiency in written and spoken English
Strong plus if you also have:
AI/ML Literacy: Understanding of Machine Learning (Supervised/Reinforcement Learning), Predictive AI, and the validation of Data Pipelines.
Proficiency in Python or experience with PySpark.
Prior experience in the e-commerce or Ad Tech ecosystem (DSPs, Audience Data, Fraud detection).
Benefits
The opportunity to shape the QA culture and architecture from the ground up.
An attractive career path on either a management or an individual contributor track.
Genuine learning, training and development opportunities, supported by regular performance reviews
Competitive compensation and generous paid time off.
Work-from-anywhere flexibility
Opportunities to develop expertise in building cutting-edge predictive AI applications.
missing_skills: Machine Learning, Mongodb, Microservices, Nosql, Appium, Aws, Sql, Cypress, Zephyr, Node.Js

title: Senior Software Test Automation Engineer — Medical Device Verification & Validation (IRC274691) IRC274691
description:
Description

Location: Erlangen (onsite, relocation is required)

We are looking for a Senior Software Test Automation Engineer to own and drive software Verification & Validation (V&V) for advanced medical systems used in surgical environments. You’ll lead a team of V&V engineers, define quality strategy, and ensure our software meets the highest standards for safety, performance, and regulatory compliance (IEC 62304).

This is a leadership role with hands-on impact — ideal for someone who thrives in regulated environments, has experience with test automation, and enjoys working closely with cross-functional teams across development, quality, and systems engineering.

About the Client:

Our client is a global leader in eye care, dedicated to improving lives by enhancing sight. With a diverse portfolio of innovative products—including contact lenses, eye care solutions, and surgical instruments for cataract and retina procedures—they serve customers in more than 140 countries. By advancing technologies and solutions, they continue to shape the future of eye health worldwide.

About the Project:

Our client is now enhancing their medical devices with advanced connectivity features and cloud-based services. Because next-generation adoption in the field is gradual, the project must ensure smooth integration of both legacy and modern systems within the same environment.

The mission is to design and deliver a comprehensive set of tools, services, and libraries that allow seamless interoperability of existing devices with cloud and on-premises infrastructures—ensuring data integrity, security, and reliability across all systems.

Requirements


  • At least 7+ years in software testing, with 3+ years in a lead or managerial role.
  • Strong background in regulated domains (medical preferred; automotive, aerospace also valuable).
  • Hands-on experience with test management tools (e.g., Polarion, Azure DevOps).
  • Experience in automation scripting, ideally with Python.
  • Strong understanding of software development lifecycle models
  • Excellent communication, leadership, and problem-solving skills.
  • German fluency required


Nice to Have


  • ISTQB Advanced certification or equivalent.
  • Familiarity with cybersecurity testing, safety-critical systems, or surgical software.
  • Knowledge of risk-based testing and traceability frameworks in medical environments.


Job responsibilities


  • Define and execute a comprehensive V&V strategy across unit, integration, system, and acceptance levels.
  • Align testing with system requirements, risk analysis, and quality standards.
  • Oversee creation and maintenance of test plans, test protocols, and traceable documentation.
  • Lead and mentor a cross-functional team of testers and V&V engineers.
  • Select and implement appropriate automation tools and frameworks (e.g., Python, Ranorex).
  • Facilitate defect triage, manage issue resolution, and support test execution.
  • Ensure audit readiness and support regulatory submissions alongside quality and RA teams.
  • Visit the office in Erlangen


What we offer

Culture of caring. At GlobalLogic, we prioritize a culture of caring. Across every region and department, at every level, we consistently put people first. From day one, you’ll experience an inclusive culture of acceptance and belonging, where you’ll have the chance to build meaningful connections with collaborative teammates, supportive managers, and compassionate leaders.

Learning and development. We are committed to your continuous learning and development. You’ll learn and grow daily in an environment with many opportunities to try new things, sharpen your skills, and advance your career at GlobalLogic. With our Career Navigator tool as just one example, GlobalLogic offers a rich array of programs, training curricula, and hands-on opportunities to grow personally and professionally.

Interesting & meaningful work. GlobalLogic is known for engineering impact for and with clients around the world. As part of our team, you’ll have the chance to work on projects that matter. Each is a unique opportunity to engage your curiosity and creative problem-solving skills as you help clients reimagine what’s possible and bring new solutions to market. In the process, you’ll have the privilege of working on some of the most cutting-edge and impactful solutions shaping the world today.

Balance and flexibility. We believe in the importance of balance and flexibility. With many functional career areas, roles, and work arrangements, you can explore ways of achieving the perfect balance between your work and life. Your life extends beyond the office, and we always do our best to help you integrate and balance the best of work and life, having fun along the way!

High-trust organization. We are a high-trust organization where integrity is key. By joining GlobalLogic, you’re placing your trust in a safe, reliable, and ethical global company. Integrity and trust are a cornerstone of our value proposition to our employees and clients. You will find truthfulness, candor, and integrity in everything we do.

About GlobalLogic

GlobalLogic, a Hitachi Group Company, is a trusted digital engineering partner to the world’s largest and most forward-thinking companies. Since 2000, we’ve been at the forefront of the digital revolution – helping create some of the most innovative and widely used digital products and experiences. Today we continue to collaborate with clients in transforming businesses and redefining industries through intelligent products, platforms, and services.

title: Software Test Engineer
description:
By clicking the “Apply” button, I understand that my employment application process with Takeda will commence and that the information I provide in my application will be processed in line with Takeda’s Privacy Notice and Terms of Use. I further attest that all information I submit in my employment application is true to the best of my knowledge.

Job Description:

Software Test Engineer:

The Future Begins Here:

At Takeda, we are creating a future-ready organization that uses data and digital to meet the needs of patients, our people, and the planet. We need your help to make this happen. Join our new Innovation Capability Center (ICC) in Bratislava, Slovakia.

In this role at our state-of-the-art center, you will have the opportunity to grow your skills and create solutions that will benefit patients around the world. Become the heart of our internal innovation engine.

At Takeda we unite in diversity :

Takeda is committed to creating an inclusive workplace, where individuals are recognized for the diverse backgrounds and abilities they bring to our company. We are continually improving workplace experience and accessibility for everyone, and welcome applications from all qualified candidates. Here, you will feel welcomed, respected, and valued as an important contributor to our Team.

The Opportunity:

As a Software Test Engineer, you'll use your technical and teamwork skills, knowledge of testing and test automation, tools and methods to help deploy and improve Data Models and Products. You will align and integrate well with testers, developers, engineers, analysts, scrum masters, delivery managers and other stakeholders.

Responsibilities:

  • Review user stories and evaluate their acceptance criteria.
  • Work closely with others to recognize the potential for any operational issues, assess risks, and help to resolve issues before the new software is complete.
  • Cooperate with other teams to understand full end-to-end use-cases to meet cross-functional requirements.
  • Define, inform, and educate the team on best practices for automated testing methodologies, development workflow improvements, continuous integration/deployment, and release management.
  • Create test approaches, test plans, test scenarios, test cases and automated test scripts for new or changed software.
  • Implement software tests, using either manual or automated approaches.
  • Run diverse sets of tests on new or changed software products to ensure they satisfy all specifications and requirements and evaluate results.
  • Write detailed, high quality defect reports for any issues encountered during testing activities.
  • Provide understandable test reports.

Skills and Qualifications:

  • Bachelor’s degree in relevant field, or other relevant work experience.
  • 4+ years of relevant professional experience in data testing with a focus on test automation.
  • Solid experience with Python, relational databases, and SQL.
  • Experience with Databricks and PySpark is an advantage.
  • Basic experience with version control systems like Git (pull requests, branching, code review).
  • Ability to clearly document test results and raise defects.
  • Good in analyzing problems and developing solutions.
  • Interest in the newest testing and test automation trends and best practices.
  • Proficient in both oral and written communication in English.
  • Team player with innovative thinking.

What Takeda Can Offer You:

At Takeda, you may build your career, while contributing to better people’s lives. Expect trust driven culture built around Integrity, Fairness, Honesty and Perseverance. Joining ICC will give you access to high end technology, training and colleagues who will support your growth.

Salary:

As a motivated employee, you should be compensated appropriately. The minimum salary for this position is € 2650: per month (full time), but your final remuneration package may be higher depending on your qualifications and experience.

Benefits:

Here are a few benefits our employees are enjoying at Takeda. To get a full picture of what we are offering, follow this link.

  • Cafeteria
  • Medical - High standard medical care
  • Bridge days
  • Summer Hours
  • Multisport Card

description:
🌍 Remote-friendly · Outcome-driven

Want to shape a product used by millions - without being tied to office walls or fixed hours?

At BlueThrone, we focus on outcomes, not time tracking. Work from wherever you’re most productive, manage your own schedule, and take time off when you need it. What matters is the quality you ship.

About BlueThrone

We don’t just build apps.
We scale indie mobile products into global businesses.

With 80M+ downloads, 20M+ MAU, and $14M ARR - all grown organically - we operate at scale while staying lean and focused. We move fast, think long-term, and take pride in shipping products people genuinely love.

Our team is made up of builders: engineers, product thinkers, and growth experts who care deeply about craft, ownership, and real impact.

The product & your role 💭

You’ll be working on a fast-growing social discovery mobile app designed to help people - mainly teenagers - connect, make friends, and build real social connections in a safe and engaging environment.

The product is highly interactive and UI-driven, with real-time user interactions, social mechanics, and a strong focus on experience. It’s used daily by a young, active audience, which means quality, stability, and trust matter a lot - even small issues are felt immediately by users.

The team is small, product-focused, and moves fast. There’s very little formal documentation, so QA is deeply involved in understanding how the product behaves, spotting gaps early, and shaping quality standards as the product evolves.

This is a hands-on, high-impact QA role. You’ll own quality end-to-end and work closely with engineers, designers, and product partners to make sure every release feels smooth, intuitive, and reliable.

We’re not looking for someone who just executes test cases.
We want someone who thinks like a user, asks the right questions, and takes real ownership of product quality 🚀

What you’ll be doing

  • Owning product quality across mobile and web

  • Designing and running test scenarios that reflect real user behavior

  • Performing regression, smoke, and exploratory testing

  • Validating APIs and integrations to ensure smooth end-to-end flows

  • Identifying edge cases, documenting issues clearly, and following them through

  • Improving testing practices as the product and team scale

  • Collaborating closely across teams - QA here is part of the build process, not an afterthought

What you'll need to succeed:

  • 5+ years of experience in QA, with a strong focus on mobile testing

  • At least 2 years of hands-on web testing experience

  • Hands-on experience testing complex, consumer-facing mobile apps

  • Experience working with data-heavy, feature-rich products

  • Familiarity with tools like Jira, Postman, Swagger (or similar)

  • A sharp eye for detail, paired with strong prioritization skills

  • An ownership mindset - you don’t wait to be told what to test

  • You ask great questions, raise flags early, and love clear communication

  • You care about the product, not just the test plan

You’ll thrive here if you:

  • Enjoy ownership without heavy process or bureaucracy

  • Like working closely with teams but also value focused, independent work

  • Can zoom out to see the product as a whole, then zoom in on details

  • See QA as a strategic role, not a support function

  • Want to work on a product with real users, real scale, and real momentum

  • Care deeply about getting things right - and improving them over time

The interview process 🪜

title: QA Engineer
description:
🌍 Remote-friendly · Outcome-driven

Want to shape a product used by millions - without being tied to office walls or fixed hours?

At BlueThrone, we focus on outcomes, not time tracking. Work from wherever you’re most productive, manage your own schedule, and take time off when you need it. What matters is the quality you ship.

About BlueThrone

We don’t just build apps.
We scale indie mobile products into global businesses.

With 80M+ downloads, 20M+ MAU, and $14M ARR - all grown organically - we operate at scale while staying lean and focused. We move fast, think long-term, and take pride in shipping products people genuinely love.

Our team is made up of builders: engineers, product thinkers, and growth experts who care deeply about craft, ownership, and real impact.

The product & your role 💭

You’ll be working on a fast-growing social discovery mobile app designed to help people - mainly teenagers - connect, make friends, and build real social connections in a safe and engaging environment.

The product is highly interactive and UI-driven, with real-time user interactions, social mechanics, and a strong focus on experience. It’s used daily by a young, active audience, which means quality, stability, and trust matter a lot - even small issues are felt immediately by users.

The team is small, product-focused, and moves fast. There’s very little formal documentation, so QA is deeply involved in understanding how the product behaves, spotting gaps early, and shaping quality standards as the product evolves.

This is a hands-on, high-impact QA role. You’ll own quality end-to-end and work closely with engineers, designers, and product partners to make sure every release feels smooth, intuitive, and reliable.

We’re not looking for someone who just executes test cases.
We want someone who thinks like a user, asks the right questions, and takes real ownership of product quality 🚀

What you’ll be doing

  • Owning product quality across mobile and web

  • Designing and running test scenarios that reflect real user behavior

  • Performing regression, smoke, and exploratory testing

  • Validating APIs and integrations to ensure smooth end-to-end flows

  • Identifying edge cases, documenting issues clearly, and following them through

  • Improving testing practices as the product and team scale

  • Collaborating closely across teams - QA here is part of the build process, not an afterthought

What you'll need to succeed:

  • 5+ years of experience in QA, with a strong focus on mobile testing

  • At least 2 years of hands-on web testing experience

  • Hands-on experience testing complex, consumer-facing mobile apps

  • Experience working with data-heavy, feature-rich products

  • Familiarity with tools like Jira, Postman, Swagger (or similar)

  • A sharp eye for detail, paired with strong prioritization skills

  • An ownership mindset - you don’t wait to be told what to test

  • You ask great questions, raise flags early, and love clear communication

  • You care about the product, not just the test plan

You’ll thrive here if you:

  • Enjoy ownership without heavy process or bureaucracy

  • Like working closely with teams but also value focused, independent work

  • Can zoom out to see the product as a whole, then zoom in on details

  • See QA as a strategic role, not a support function

  • Want to work on a product with real users, real scale, and real momentum

  • Care deeply about getting things right - and improving them over time

The interview process 🪜

  1. Intro call with our People team (45 min)

  2. Technical deep-dive with our QA Engineer (60 min)

  3. Meeting with Tech Lead (45 min)

  4. Final conversation with our CTO (45 min)

 🚀 We move fast and flex around your availability. Most processes take 3-4 weeks.

Equal opportunities for everyone 💖

We believe the best teams are diverse teams. We welcome applicants from all backgrounds and experiences. We consider all candidates regardless of age, ethnicity, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, family or parental status, national origin, veteran status, neurodiversity, or disability. If you need reasonable adjustments at any point in the application or interview process, please let us know.

title: Expert Quality Assurance (QA) Engineer
description:
At Quento Technologies S.A., the ICT arm of the Qualco Group, we deliver comprehensive and innovative solutions across AI, Digital Engineering, Cloud, and Cybersecurity, helping businesses accelerate digital transformation. With a presence in Greece, Luxembourg, and Belgium, and backed by the expertise of the Qualco Group, we combine deep technical knowledge with strategic partnerships to support business growth.

At Quento Technologies S.A., we empower our people to innovate and lead in delivering transformative ICT solutions to our clients worldwide. Quento Technologies S.A. seeks a highly motivated and experienced Expert Quality Assurance (QA) Engineer to develop and implement QA processes, conduct audits and ensure compliance with quality standards.

Responsibilities:

  • Data Quality Framework
    • Develop, implement, and maintain the annual data quality framework.
    • Organize and chair events, workshops, and knowledge-sharing sessions with contributors to improve data quality across the organization.
    • Monitor, evaluate, and report on data quality KPIs and progress against established standards.
  • Portal UAT Framework
    • Develop and implement a structured User Acceptance Testing (UAT) framework for the portal.
    • Coordinate test planning, execution, and reporting in collaboration with business users and technical teams.
  • Service Catalogue & Process Descriptions
    • Establish and maintain a clear Service Catalogue for the portal team.
  • Ensuring that all activities and duties comply fully with regulatory requirements, including the Group Anti-Bribery and Corruption Policy.

Requirements

  • University degree in Information Systems, Computer Science, Engineering, Business Administration, or related field;
  • Minimum 9 years of proven experience in Quality Assurance, preferably in data management, portals, or enterprise systems;
  • Excellent knowledge and hands-on experience with Quality Assurance Processes:
    • Implement, operate, and maintain QA processes within the portal team;
    • Conduct quality reviews and audits to ensure deliverables meet defined standards and business requirements;
    • Ensure compliance with quality standards, guidelines, and best practices;
    • Promote a culture of quality through continuous improvement initiatives;
  • Knowledge of QA methodologies, frameworks, and tools;
  • Experience with UAT planning and execution;
  • Strong analytical and problem-solving skills;
  • Excellent communication, facilitation, and stakeholder management skills;
  • Excellent verbal and written communication in English.

Benefits

This role is an on - site opportunity in Bratislava, Slovakia.

CV submitted in English.

Your race, gender identity and expression, age ethnicity or disability make no difference in Quento Technologies S.A. we want to attract, develop, promote, and retain the best people based only on their ability and behavior.

Disclaimer: Quento Technologies S.A. collects and processes personal data in accordance with the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). We are bound to use the information provided within your job application for recruitment purposes only and not to share these with any third parties. For more details on the processing of your personal data during the Recruitment procedure, please be informed in the Recruitment Notice, before the submission of your application.
